hubId.name: hubId
hubId.description: HUB ENCLOSURE Group The address of the hub enclosure in MAC address format. This is the supervisor's MAC address.

hubType.name: hubType
hubType.description: The type of enclosure; the number of slots in the enclosure.

hubName.name: hubName
hubName.description: The name of the Access/One enclosure.

hubSerNumber.name: hubSerNumber
hubSerNumber.description: The serial number of the hub.

hubIPAddr.name: hubIPAddr
hubIPAddr.description: The IP address used to communicate with the SNMP agent in the Supervisor.

hubTempStatus.name: hubTempStatus
hubTempStatus.description: Indicates whether the temperature of at least one card in the enclosure is out of range.

hubPollTime.name: hubPollTime
hubPollTime.description: The time in tenths of seconds between polls of hub cards by the supervisor.

hubResetAction.name: hubResetAction
hubResetAction.description: When this internet-object is SET to a value of requested, resetAllCards, or forceLoad, the hub resets (according to the specific request), and after resetting locally sets the value of this internet-object to not-requested. Initially its value is not-requested.

hubAFS.name: hubAFS
hubAFS.description: Indicates whether airflow inside the enclosure is normal. This applies only to enclosures with an Air Flow Sensor (AFS) installed and a supervisor capable of detecting the signal from this sensor (currently only the ASM-710 and ASM-760).

ensupStaticNetConfig.name: ensupStaticNetConfig
ensupStaticNetConfig.description: CARD Group ensup: Ethernet Supervisor The configured status of the interface between the net module(s) and the backbone.

ensupDynamicNetStatus.name: ensupDynamicNetStatus
ensupDynamicNetStatus.description: The dynamically changed configuration status of the interface between the net module(s) and the backbone.

ensupNetBridgeSlot.name: ensupNetBridgeSlot
ensupNetBridgeSlot.description: The relative group (slot) containing a local bridge by which the modules access the backbone (relevant only if the value of ensupStaticNetConfig is 'sup-bridge').

ensupCarrierCounter.name: ensupCarrierCounter
ensupCarrierCounter.description: The number of times that carrier sense was on when sampled every 2 ms (used in conjunction with a1gUpTime).

ensupNetUtilization.name: ensupNetUtilization
ensupNetUtilization.description: The percentage of time that carrier sense was on; the percentage is expressed to the nearest tenth (as XXX.X%).

ensupNetUtilThreshold.name: ensupNetUtilThreshold
ensupNetUtilThreshold.description: The threshold for ensupNetUtilization (sends a trap when exceeded).Percentage utilization to the nearest whole integer.

a1gTable.name: a1gTable
a1gTable.description: a1g: Access/1 Group TABLE Row selection: the card's relative position in the enclosure, starting at 1.

a1gSlotId.name: a1gSlotId
a1gSlotId.description: The card's relative position in the enclosure, starting at 1.

a1gPorts.name: a1gPorts
a1gPorts.description: The number of ports on a card.

a1gOperStatus.name: a1gOperStatus
a1gOperStatus.description: states the module goes through when doing power-on diagnostics.

a1gTempStatus.name: a1gTempStatus
a1gTempStatus.description: An indication whether the card's temperature is too high.

a1gEthBusAdmAction.name: a1gEthBusAdmAction
a1gEthBusAdmAction.description: The administrative status of a module's Ethernet Bus interface (action). For an ASM320, if a1gEthBusMgmtStatus == lockedByJumper, then values of this attribute cannot be set.

a1gEthBusMgmtStatus.name: a1gEthBusMgmtStatus
a1gEthBusMgmtStatus.description: The management status of a module's Ethernet bus interface.

a1gNetMgmtBusOperStatus.name: a1gNetMgmtBusOperStatus
a1gNetMgmtBusOperStatus.description: The operational status of the network management interface from the supervisor to the module (the control bus).

a1gProductType.name: a1gProductType
a1gProductType.description: The product type of an A/1 card.

a1gUpTime.name: a1gUpTime
a1gUpTime.description: The elapsed time since the module started operating.

a1gResets.name: a1gResets
a1gResets.description: The number of times a module has been reset.

a1gResetAction.name: a1gResetAction
a1gResetAction.description: When this internet-object is SET to one of the request values, the card resets, and after resetting retains the value that was SET. Initially its value is not-requested.

configTable.name: configTable
configTable.description: config: Access/1 Group Configuration TABLE Row selection: the card's relative position in the enclosure, starting at 1.

configSlotId.name: configSlotId
configSlotId.description: The card's relative position in the enclosure, starting at 1.

configFaultActionType.name: configFaultActionType
configFaultActionType.description: The action to be taken by the Supervisor following a fault on a card.

configRetries.name: configRetries
configRetries.description: The maximum number of times a reset is attempted when configFaultAction is set to reset (no further attempts are made once the reset is successful).

configPowerUpMode.name: configPowerUpMode
configPowerUpMode.description: The actions taken by the module immediately after power up (pod is Power On Diagnostics).

a1imTable.name: a1imTable
a1imTable.description: a1im: Access/1 Intelligent Module TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object a1imSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1.

a1imSlotId.name: a1imSlotId
a1imSlotId.description: The relative slot position of a card, starting at 1.

a1imMACAddr.name: a1imMACAddr
a1imMACAddr.description: The module's MAC address (for a bridge, its first network interface). May be (e.g., for the TRC-410) a unique id chosen from the set of MAC addresses.

a1imPodDiagnosticMsg.name: a1imPodDiagnosticMsg
a1imPodDiagnosticMsg.description: A text message describing a power-on-diagnostic state.

a1imHaltReason.name: a1imHaltReason
a1imHaltReason.description: The last specific halt reason detected by the card.

a1imDebugRegisters.name: a1imDebugRegisters
a1imDebugRegisters.description: A set of 14 80186 registers used for debugging purposes. These are CS, IP, FLAG, AX, BX, CX, DX, SP, BP, SI, DI, DS, ES, and SS.

tplTable.name: tplTable
tplTable.description: tpl: Transport Layer TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object tplSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1.

tplSlotId.name: tplSlotId
tplSlotId.description: The relative slot position of a card, starting at 1.

tplIPAddress.name: tplIPAddress
tplIPAddress.description: The card's IP address (only applies to TCP/IP)

tplNiuName.name: tplNiuName
tplNiuName.description: The card's Niu name (only applies to ISO)

tplProtocolType.name: tplProtocolType
tplProtocolType.description: The type of transport protocol used by the module.

tplSuprvPollStatus.name: tplSuprvPollStatus
tplSuprvPollStatus.description: Indicates whether the module has responded to supervisor polling over Ethernet.

imenEthBusTable.name: imenEthBusTable
imenEthBusTable.description: imen: Intelligent Module Ethernet Datalink TABLE (Ethernet Bus interface) Row selection: the value of the internet-object imenSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1.

imenSlotId.name: imenSlotId
imenSlotId.description: The relative position of the card in the enclosure, starting from 1.

imenTransmitPkts.name: imenTransmitPkts
imenTransmitPkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted.

imenReceivePkts.name: imenReceivePkts
imenReceivePkts.description: The total number of packets received.

imenCRCErrors.name: imenCRCErrors
imenCRCErrors.description: The number of packets received with CRC errors.

imenCollisions.name: imenCollisions
imenCollisions.description: The number of packets transmitted with collision detected.

brdgTable.name: brdgTable
brdgTable.description: brdg: Bridge TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object brdgSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1, plus the relative interface, brdgIfId, starting at 1.

brdgSlotId.name: brdgSlotId
brdgSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing this card.

brdgIfId.name: brdgIfId
brdgIfId.description: The relative interface (from 1) of this entry (see the appropriate hardware specification to determine which interface is 1, 2, etc.).

brdgIfFault.name: brdgIfFault
brdgIfFault.description: Bridge faults (note these are interface specific).

brdgIfMACAddr.name: brdgIfMACAddr
brdgIfMACAddr.description: The MAC address of the bridge's specific interface

ecTable.name: ecTable
ecTable.description: ec: Ethernet Concentrator TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object ecSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1.

ecSlotId.name: ecSlotId
ecSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing this card.

ecCarrierCounter.name: ecCarrierCounter
ecCarrierCounter.description: The number of times carrier was sensed when sampled every 2 ms.

ecFanStatus.name: ecFanStatus
ecFanStatus.description: The status of the Temp/Flex mount adaptor fan (on the ASM-800 (fiber EC) only).

netTable.name: netTable
netTable.description: net: NET Card TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object netSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1.

netSlotId.name: netSlotId
netSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing this card.

netBackboneType.name: netBackboneType
netBackboneType.description: The type of backbone to which the NET interface is attached.

netFault.name: netFault
netFault.description: An interface fault at various points between the module and the attached backbone.

netBackboneStatus.name: netBackboneStatus
netBackboneStatus.description: Backbone interface status: the status of the interface or interfaces to the backbone.

brnTable.name: brnTable
brnTable.description: brn: Buffer Repeater NET Card TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object brnSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1, plus the relative interface, brnIfId (1 or 2).

brnSlotId.name: brnSlotId
brnSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing this card.

brnIfId.name: brnIfId
brnIfId.description: The relative interface (from 1) containing this card; interface 1 is the Ethernet Bus interface.

brnIfEthDLCStatus.name: brnIfEthDLCStatus
brnIfEthDLCStatus.description: The Ethernet Data Link Control status of the last transmission to the segment attached to the buffered repeater net card.

brnCarrierCounter.name: brnCarrierCounter
brnCarrierCounter.description: The number of times carrier was sensed when sampled every 1 ms.

brnCarrierTimeInterval.name: brnCarrierTimeInterval
brnCarrierTimeInterval.description: The time interval over which brnCarrierCounter counts.

brnTransmitPkts.name: brnTransmitPkts
brnTransmitPkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted.

brnReceivePkts.name: brnReceivePkts
brnReceivePkts.description: The total number of packets received.

brnCRCErrors.name: brnCRCErrors
brnCRCErrors.description: The number of packets received with CRC errors.

brnPktsAborted16Colls.name: brnPktsAborted16Colls
brnPktsAborted16Colls.description: The number of packets aborted because of 16 consecutive collisions detected.

brnShortPkts.name: brnShortPkts
brnShortPkts.description: The total number of short packets received.

brnAlignmentErrors.name: brnAlignmentErrors
brnAlignmentErrors.description: The total number of packets received with alignment errors: the number of frames received that are not an integral number of octets and do not pass the FCS check.

brnOverflows.name: brnOverflows
brnOverflows.description: The number of packets received that had to be discarded due to errors in bit frequency resulting in overflow.

brnUnderflows.name: brnUnderflows
brnUnderflows.description: The number of packets received that had to be discarded due to errors in bit frequency resulting in underflow.

tr16cTable.name: tr16cTable
tr16cTable.description: tr16c: Token Ring Concentrator Card TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object tr16cSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1.

tr16cSlotId.name: tr16cSlotId
tr16cSlotId.description: The relative slot number, starting at 1, of the concentrator.

tr16cTier.name: tr16cTier
tr16cTier.description: 17,32 RelayID Indicates the management level of functionality (tier) of this concentrator.

tr16cOperState.name: tr16cOperState
tr16cOperState.description: The operational state of the ring.

tr16cRingNumber.name: tr16cRingNumber
tr16cRingNumber.description: The ring number assigned when configuring a bridge.

tr16cManufacturerID.name: tr16cManufacturerID
tr16cManufacturerID.description: The Organization Unique Identifier as defined in IEEE 802.1A, Overview and Architecture. This is the first 24 bits of UB's MAC address identifying UB uniquely worldwide and is a constant equal to 00DD00 in hexadecimal.

tr16cManufacturerProductID.name: tr16cManufacturerProductID
tr16cManufacturerProductID.description: A string of ASCII characters representing the concentrator's product identifier (i.e., a name identifying an enumeration of a1gProductType). Some examples are 'trc-410-1' and 'trc-410-2'.

tr16cManufProductVers.name: tr16cManufProductVers
tr16cManufProductVers.description: A string that is unique for a specific manufacturerProductID that identifies a concentrators's hardware and firmware versions. The two octets are non-negative integers with values from 0 through 255. If a version does not apply then the version number is zero. One is the first applicable version number. The first octet is the hardware version and the second is the firmware version.

tr16cActiveMonitorPortNumber.name: tr16cActiveMonitorPortNumber
tr16cActiveMonitorPortNumber.description: The relative port number of the active monitor for this ring. Its value is 0 if the active monitor is not attached to any port on this concentrator.

tr16cRingSpeed.name: tr16cRingSpeed
tr16cRingSpeed.description: 17 RingSpeed The current concentrator operating speed of either 4 or 16 Mbps. Note that each concentrator in a ring must be configured with the same value of this attribute.

tr16cLLCFrames.name: tr16cLLCFrames
tr16cLLCFrames.description: 26 TotalLLCFramesThe total number of transmitted frames that are not MAC level management frames.

tr16cMACFrames.name: tr16cMACFrames
tr16cMACFrames.description: 26 TotalMACFramesThe total number of transmitted frames that are MAC level management frames.

tr16cOctets.name: tr16cOctets
tr16cOctets.description: 26 TotalOctetsThe total number of octets transmitted.

tr16cMulticastFrames.name: tr16cMulticastFrames
tr16cMulticastFrames.description: 26 TotalMulticastFramesThe total number of frames with a destination address that is either a Functional Group Address or a Group Address.

tr16cBroadcastFrames.name: tr16cBroadcastFrames
tr16cBroadcastFrames.description: 26 TotalBroadcastFramesThe total number of frames with a destination address that is a Broadcast Address.

tr16cFrameCheckSequences.name: tr16cFrameCheckSequences
tr16cFrameCheckSequences.description: 26,27 TotalFrameCheckSequenceThe total number of packets with an FCS error.

tr16cAutoPartitionEnableTimer.name: tr16cAutoPartitionEnableTimer
tr16cAutoPartitionEnableTimer.description: 25 AutoPartitionEnableTimer *a Indicates the period of time to wait until re-enabling a 'beacon detected' port. the default value is 0 seconds

tr16cAutoPartitionHoldTimer.name: tr16cAutoPartitionHoldTimer
tr16cAutoPartitionHoldTimer.description: 25 AutoPartitionHoldTimer *a Indicates the amount of time to wait until starting the beacon detect process. The default value is 0 seconds.

tr16cAutoPartitionRetries.name: tr16cAutoPartitionRetries
tr16cAutoPartitionRetries.description: 25 AutoPartitionThreshold *a Indicates the number of times a port can be temporarily locked by the beacon detect process prior to being permanently locked. The default value is 3.

tr16cLLCSamples.name: tr16cLLCSamples
tr16cLLCSamples.description: 26,27 BandwidthUtilizationA count of the number of times that an LLC packet was present when sampling every millisecond.

tr16cMACSamples.name: tr16cMACSamples
tr16cMACSamples.description: 26,27 BandwidthUtilizationA count of the number of times that a MAC frame was present when sampling every millisecond.

tr16cUpTimeMS.name: tr16cUpTimeMS
tr16cUpTimeMS.description: 26,27 BandwidthUtilization The elapsed time in milliseconds since the concentrator started operating.

tr16cResetDurableUserAttrs.name: tr16cResetDurableUserAttrs
tr16cResetDurableUserAttrs.description: A request to copy the default values stored in durable memory to the User Durable attributes also in durable memory. The User attributes affected are tr16cRingSpeed, tr16p1AllowInsert, tr16p1ForceInsert, tr16cAutoPartitionEnableTimer, tr16cAutoPartitionHoldTimer, and tr16cAutoPartitionRetries.

tr16reTable.name: tr16reTable
tr16reTable.description: tr16re: Token Ring Concentrator Ring Error TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object tr16cSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1. Contains ring error monitor non-isolating errors.

tr16reSlotId.name: tr16reSlotId
tr16reSlotId.description: The relative slot in the hub enclosure, starting at 1.

ecpTable.name: ecpTable
ecpTable.description: PORT Group ecp: Ethernet Port TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object ecpSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1, plus a relative port identifier, starting at 1.

ecpSlotId.name: ecpSlotId
ecpSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing the card.

ecpPortId.name: ecpPortId
ecpPortId.description: The relative port (from 1) on the card.

ecpMgmtStatus.name: ecpMgmtStatus
ecpMgmtStatus.description: The management status of an Ethernet port.

ecpAdmAction.name: ecpAdmAction
ecpAdmAction.description: The administrative status of an Ethernet port.

ecpCarrierCounter.name: ecpCarrierCounter
ecpCarrierCounter.description: The number of times carrier was sensed on the port when sampled every 2 ms.

ecfpTable.name: ecfpTable
ecfpTable.description: ecfp: Ethernet Concentrator Fiber Port TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object ecfpSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1, plus the relative port identifier, ecfpPortId, starting at 1.

ecfpSlotId.name: ecfpSlotId
ecfpSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing the card.

ecfpPortId.name: ecfpPortId
ecfpPortId.description: The relative port (from 1) on the card.

ecfpMACAddr.name: ecfpMACAddr
ecfpMACAddr.description: The latest source MAC address from packets received from the MAC side of the AUI

ecfpTxIdleTime.name: ecfpTxIdleTime
ecfpTxIdleTime.description: The elapsed time since the last packet was transmitted.

ec10btpTable.name: ec10btpTable
ec10btpTable.description: ec10btp: Ethernet Concentrator 10BaseT Port TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object ec10btpSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1, plus the relative port identifier, ec10btpPortId, starting at 1.

ec10btpSlotId.name: ec10btpSlotId
ec10btpSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing the card.

ec10btpPortId.name: ec10btpPortId
ec10btpPortId.description: The relative port (from 1) on the card.

ec10btpLinkTestStatus.name: ec10btpLinkTestStatus
ec10btpLinkTestStatus.description: The result of the link integrity test.

ec10btpLinkTestAction.name: ec10btpLinkTestAction
ec10btpLinkTestAction.description: A request to unlock the link integrity test (which is a continuous test).

trcpTable.name: trcpTable
trcpTable.description: trcp: Token Ring Concentrator Port TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object trcpSlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1, plus a relative port identifier starting at 1.

trcpSlotId.name: trcpSlotId
trcpSlotId.description: The relative slot (from 1) containing the card.

trcpPortId.name: trcpPortId
trcpPortId.description: The relative port (from 1) on the card.

trcpAdmAction.name: trcpAdmAction
trcpAdmAction.description: The administrative status of a token ring port. It reflects only administrative status.

trcpOperStatus.name: trcpOperStatus
trcpOperStatus.description: The operational status of a token ring port.

tr16p1Table.name: tr16p1Table
tr16p1Table.description: tr16p1: Token Ring Concentrator Port Tier 1 TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object tr16p1SlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1 plus the value of tr16p1PortId, which contains the relative position of a port within a card, starting at 1.

tr16p1SlotId.name: tr16p1SlotId
tr16p1SlotId.description: The relative position (starting at 1) of the concentrator's slot within the enclosure.

tr16p1PortId.name: tr16p1PortId
tr16p1PortId.description: The relative port on the card starting at 1. Ports 1-12 are ring station ports, 13 is the expansion in port, and 14 is the expansion out port.

tr16p1InsertionState.name: tr16p1InsertionState
tr16p1InsertionState.description: The end result of tr16p1AllowInsert, tr16p1ForceInsert, and tr16p1PhantomState, i.e., inserted means tr16p1ForceInsert | tr16p1AllowInsert & tr16p1PhantomState, where tr16p1ForceInsert is true if requested, tr16p1AllowInsert is true if requested, and tr16p1PhantomState is true if phantomPresent.

tr16p1AllowInsert.name: tr16p1AllowInsert
tr16p1AllowInsert.description: 19 RingStationPortAction *aAn action that allows an RS port to insert onto its ring if both phantom voltages are present (tr16p1PhantomState is phantomPresent).20 ExpansionInPortAction *aWhen not allowed, this bypass forces a 'loop-back' to occur on the XI port, and does not allow concentrators to insert onto their rings.21 ExpansionOutPortAction *aWhen not allowed this bypass forces a 'loop-back' to occur on the XO port so that an attached ASM400 or ASM410 is not inserted when phantom voltage is detected.

tr16p1ForceInsert.name: tr16p1ForceInsert
tr16p1ForceInsert.description: 19 RingStationPortInsert *aWhen forcedInsertion, forces an RS port to insert onto its ring regardless of whether phantom voltage or other conditions are detected. This is used to support passive devices, such as the IBM MSAU, in order to support the Satellite expansion capability.19 ExpansionInPortInsert *aWhen set, inserts the XI port onto the ring regardless of whether phantom voltage is present.21 ExpansionOutPortInsert *aForces XI port to insert on the network.

tr16p1PhantomState.name: tr16p1PhantomState
tr16p1PhantomState.description: 19 ExpansionInPhantomDetect Indicates the XI port detects phantom voltage being provided.20 ExpansionOutPhantomLoadDetect The status of the phantom voltage provided by the XO port (XO->XI or XO->RS (satellite)).

tr16p2Table.name: tr16p2Table
tr16p2Table.description: tr16p2: Token Ring Concentrator Port Tiers 2,3 TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object tr16p2SlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1 plus the value of tr16p2PortId, which contains the relative position of a port within a card, starting at 1.

tr16p2SlotId.name: tr16p2SlotId
tr16p2SlotId.description: The relative position (starting at 1) of the concentrator's slot within the enclosure.

tr16p2PortId.name: tr16p2PortId
tr16p2PortId.description: The relative port on the card starting at 1. Ports 1-12 are ring station ports, 13 is the expansion in port, and 14 is the expansion out port.

tr16p2OperState.name: tr16p2OperState
tr16p2OperState.description: 25 RingStationAutoPartitionState25 RingExpansionInPartitionState25 ExpansionOutAutoPartitionState Indicates whether a hard failure has occurred on a port, been detected through the beaconing procedure, and the offending port subsequently bypassed in the ring.

tr16p2BeaconDetects.name: tr16p2BeaconDetects
tr16p2BeaconDetects.description: 25 RingStationAutoPartitionCount25 ExpansionInAutoPartitionCount25 ExpansionOutAutoPartitionCount Indicates the number of beacon detects that have resulted in this port being partitioned (removed from its ring).

tr16p2LastSourceAddress.name: tr16p2LastSourceAddress
tr16p2LastSourceAddress.description: 23,27 RingStationLastSourceAddress23,27 ExpansionInLastSourceAddress23,27 ExpansionOutLastSourceAddress Address of previously attached node.

tr16p2LLCFramesTransmitted.name: tr16p2LLCFramesTransmitted
tr16p2LLCFramesTransmitted.description: 27 RingStationLLCFramesTransmitted 27 ExpansionInLLCFramesTransmitted 27 ExpansionOutLLCFramesTransmitted Total number of non-MAC Management packets transmitted.

tr16p2LLCFramesReceived.name: tr16p2LLCFramesReceived
tr16p2LLCFramesReceived.description: 27 RingStationLLCFramesReceived 27 ExpansionInLLCFramesReceived 27 ExpansionOutLLCFramesReceived Total number of non-MAC Management packets received.

tr16p2MACFramesTransmitted.name: tr16p2MACFramesTransmitted
tr16p2MACFramesTransmitted.description: 27 RingStationMACFramesTransmitted27 ExpansionInMACFramesTransmitted27 ExpansionOutMACFramesTransmitted Total number of MAC Management packets transmitted.

tr16p2MACFramesReceived.name: tr16p2MACFramesReceived
tr16p2MACFramesReceived.description: 27 RingStationMACFramesReceived27 ExpansionInMACFramesReceived27 ExpansionOutMACFramesReceived Total number of MAC Management packets received.

tr16p2OctetsTransmitted.name: tr16p2OctetsTransmitted
tr16p2OctetsTransmitted.description: 27 RingStationOctetsTransmitted27 ExpansionInOctetsTransmitted27 ExpansionOutOctetsTransmitted Total number of LLC Information octets transmitted.

tr16p2OctetsReceived.name: tr16p2OctetsReceived
tr16p2OctetsReceived.description: 27 RingStationOctetsReceived27 ExpansionInOctetsReceived27 ExpansionOutOctetsReceived Total number of LLC Information Field octets received.

tr16p2MulticastsTransmitted.name: tr16p2MulticastsTransmitted
tr16p2MulticastsTransmitted.description: 28 RingStationMulticastTransmitted 28 ExpansionInMulticastTransmitted 28 ExpansionOutMulticastTransmitted Total number of Multicast packets transmitted.

tr16p2BroadcastsTransmitted.name: tr16p2BroadcastsTransmitted
tr16p2BroadcastsTransmitted.description: 28 RingStationBroadcastTransmitted28 ExpansionOutBroadcastTransmitted28 ExpansionInBroadcastTransmitted Total number of Broadcast packets transmitted.

tr16p2FCSErrorsTransmitted.name: tr16p2FCSErrorsTransmitted
tr16p2FCSErrorsTransmitted.description: 28 RingStationFCSErrorsTransmitted28 ExpansionInFCSErrorsTransmitted28 ExpansionOutFCSErrorsTransmitted Total number of packets transmitted with an FCS error.

tr16p2FCSErrorsReceived.name: tr16p2FCSErrorsReceived
tr16p2FCSErrorsReceived.description: 28 RingStationFCSErrorsReceived28 ExpansionInFCSErrorsReceived28 ExpansionOutFCSErrorsReceived Total number of packets received with an FCS error.

tr16p2LastSourceAddressUptime.name: tr16p2LastSourceAddressUptime
tr16p2LastSourceAddressUptime.description: Time since the value of tr16p2LastSourceAddress last changed.

tr16p3Table.name: tr16p3Table
tr16p3Table.description: tr16p3: Token Ring Concentrator Port Tiers 2,3 TABLE Row selection: the value of the internet-object tr16p3SlotId, which contains the relative position of a card within an enclosure, starting at 1 plus the value of tr16p3PortId, which contains the relative position of a port within a card, starting at 1.

tr16p3SlotId.name: tr16p3SlotId
tr16p3SlotId.description: The relative position (starting at 1) of the concentrator's slot within the enclosure.

tr16p3PortId.name: tr16p3PortId
tr16p3PortId.description: The relative port on the card starting at 1. Ports 1-12 are ring station ports, 13 is the expansion in port, and 14 is the expansion out port.

trapInstanceId.name: trapInstanceId
trapInstanceId.description: TRAP Group: The attributes that may appear in the variable-bindings list of the Trap-PDU. An instance identifier that uniquely identifies an occurrence of a trap. Note that if multiple Trap-PDUs are sent to reflect the occurrence of the same trap, each contains the same value of the trapInstanceId.

trapSlotId.name: trapSlotId
trapSlotId.description: trapSource (consists of the following):The attributes required to define the source of the trap. For example, when a port is unlocked, the slot identifier and port identifier define the source of the trap. The product type is also included in case the enterprise field in the trap-PDU does not completely distinguish the characteristics of the source. The relative slot (from 1) containing the card that the trap is about.

trapProductType.name: trapProductType
trapProductType.description: The product type of the Access/One card that the trap is about.See a1gProductType for specific values.

trapPortID.name: trapPortID
trapPortID.description: The relative port (from 1) that the trap is about.

trapPortCount.name: trapPortCount
trapPortCount.description: The number of ports on a concentrator.

trapPortMask.name: trapPortMask

trpsbIpAddress.description: The IP address of a manager subscribing to traps.

trpsbActions.name: trpsbActions

moduleInserted.name: moduleInserted
moduleInserted.description: A card was inserted in the Access/One chassis.

moduleRemoved.name: moduleRemoved
moduleRemoved.description: A card was removed from the Access/One chassis.

moduleFaulty.name: moduleFaulty
moduleFaulty.description: A card has become faulty: its state changed to a1gOperStatus (moduleFault(6)).

moduleDown.name: moduleDown
moduleDown.description: A card has not responded to a supervisor poll: its state changed to a1gEthBusMgmtStatus(notResponding(4)).

moduleReset.name: moduleReset
moduleReset.description: A card has been reset: its state changed to a1gOperStatus (reset(13)).

moduleDebug.name: moduleDebug
moduleDebug.description: A card has put into debug mode: its state changed to a1gOperStatus (debugMode(4)).

moduleHighTemperature.name: moduleHighTemperature
moduleHighTemperature.description: The card's temperature has become too high: its state changed to a1gTempStatus(abnormal(2)).

ethBusUnlocked.name: ethBusUnlocked
ethBusUnlocked.description: The interface to the Ethernet bus has been unlocked: its state changed to a1gEthBusAdmAction(unlock(2)).

ethBusLocked.name: ethBusLocked
ethBusLocked.description: The interface to the Ethernet bus has been locked: its state changed to a1gEthBusAdmAction(lock(3)).

moduleNetIfEnabled.name: moduleNetIfEnabled
moduleNetIfEnabled.description: The status of the interface to the backbone has changed so that all modules (with the possible exception of the supervisor - when it is in direct mode) access the backbone through the card's net interface: a state change to netBackboneStatus(active(2)) has occurred.

moduleNetIfDisabled.name: moduleNetIfDisabled
moduleNetIfDisabled.description: The status of the interface to the backbone has changed so that there is no communication backbone through the card's net interface: a state change to netBackboneStatus(standby(6)) has occurred

moduleNetIfLoopBack.name: moduleNetIfLoopBack
moduleNetIfLoopBack.description: The status of the interface to the backbone has changed so that this card's net interface loops back traffic directed to the backbone, while the other (possible) net interface's status becomes standby: a state change to netBackboneStatus(loopback(4)) has occurred.

moduleNetIfInternalError.name: moduleNetIfInternalError
moduleNetIfInternalError.description: An internal error at the net interface has been detected: its state changed to netFault(internal(2)).

moduleNetIfExternalError.name: moduleNetIfExternalError
moduleNetIfExternalError.description: An external error at the net interface has been detected: its state changed to either netFault(auiBad(3)) or netFault(mdiBad(4)).

moduleParityError.name: moduleParityError
moduleParityError.description: An intelligent module has detected a parity error: its status has changed to a1imModuleFault (parityErr(3)).

moduleFanBad.name: moduleFanBad
moduleFanBad.description: The fan on the module is defective: its status has changed to ecFanStatus(abnormal(3)).

beaconDetected.name: beaconDetected
beaconDetected.description: The ring containing this card has begun the beacon detect process: its status has changed to tr16cOperState(beaconDetectInProgress(4)).

moduleTemperatureNormal.name: moduleTemperatureNormal
moduleTemperatureNormal.description: The card's temperature has returned to normal: its state changed from a1gTempStatus(abnormal(2)) to a1gTempStatus(normal(3)).

portUnlocked.name: portUnlocked
portUnlocked.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports have been unlocked.

portLocked.name: portLocked
portLocked.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports have been locked.

portAutoSegmented.name: portAutoSegmented
portAutoSegmented.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports have been auto-segmented by the hardware because of a fault.

portFault.name: portFault
portFault.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports have been segmented by the supervisor because of a fault.

portForced.name: portForced
portForced.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports have been forced to allow passive devices to enter the ring.

portNotForced.name: portNotForced
portNotForced.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports are no longer being forced to allow passive devices to enter the ring.

portLobeFault.name: portLobeFault
portLobeFault.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports are experiencing a lobe fault. The concentrator experiences voltage(either positive or negative) in only one of the phantom pair wires.

portLobeFaultCleared.name: portLobeFaultCleared
portLobeFaultCleared.description: One or more of the concentrator's ports are no longer experiencing a lobe fault.

portLinkTestUnlocked.name: portLinkTestUnlocked
portLinkTestUnlocked.description: The link test on one or more of the concentrator's ports has been unlocked.

portLinkTestLocked.name: portLinkTestLocked
portLinkTestLocked.description: The link test on one or more of the concentrator's ports has been locked.

badPowerSupply.name: badPowerSupply
badPowerSupply.description: At least one power module has lost its AC power. : its state changed to hubPowerSupplyStatus(acPowerAbnormal(3)).

powerSupplyHiTemp.name: powerSupplyHiTemp
powerSupplyHiTemp.description: The temperature of the power supply has become too high: its state changed to hubPowerSupplyStatus(highTemp(4)).

networkIfError.name: networkIfError
networkIfError.description: One or more of the interfaces to the network backbone are experiencing faults: its state changed to ensupDynamicNetStatus(netOrSupLoopback(6)).

networkIfOK.name: networkIfOK
networkIfOK.description: The interface to the backbone network has changed (recovered) by using a redundant connection. The state of the interface to the backbone network changed to one of ensupDynamicNetStatus(netAndSupDirect(2) | supOnly(3) | netOnly(4) | bridgeOnly(5)).

tempBad.name: tempBad
tempBad.description: The temperature in the enclosure has been reported by an enclosure temperature sensor to be out of range(possible enclosure fan failure) or the temperature of at least one card in the enclosure is out of range: the hub's state changed to hubTempStatus(abnormal(2)).

tempOK.name: tempOK
tempOK.description: The temperature of all cards in the enclosure is now in the proper range or the enclosure temperature has returned to the proper range: the hub's state changed to: hubTempStatus(normal(3))

fTPSBad.name: fTPSBad
fTPSBad.description: One or both (for a fault tolerant power supply) dc power supplies have failed. The power supply's state has changed to: hubPowerSupplyStatus(onePsModuleFailed(5)).

netUtilThreshold.name: netUtilThreshold
netUtilThreshold.description: The network utilization has been exceeded: ensupNetUtilization exceeded ensupNetUtilThreshold.

enclosureFanBad.name: enclosureFanBad
enclosureFanBad.description: The enclosure has an airflow problem (probably a defective fan): the state of hubAFS has changed to abnormal(3).

servicePortLogin.name: servicePortLogin
servicePortLogin.description: The interpreter on the netcard has detected a login command on the service port.

servicePortLogout.name: servicePortLogout
servicePortLogout.description: The interpreter on the netcard has detected a logout command on the service port.
